com.palomamobile.android.sdk.core

Enum ServiceSupport

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ServiceSupport>
      • com.palomamobile.android.sdk.core.ServiceSupport
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IServiceSupport, Serializable, Comparable<ServiceSupport>

    public enum ServiceSupport
extends Enum<ServiceSupport>
implements IServiceSupport
    Entry point to the SDK. Call init(Context) or init(ServiceSupportConfiguration) to initialize, prior to calling any other methods, a good place to do this is from within Application.onCreate(). Unless one of the init(..)} methods is called first all other methods will throw an IllegalStateException It is possible to customize most of the behaviour of this class by providing custom implementations of key components via the init(ServiceSupportConfiguration) call.

      • registerServiceManager

        public <T extends IServiceManager> void registerServiceManager(Class<T> intrface,
                                                      T serviceManager)
        Description copied from interface: IServiceSupport
        Registers a new IServiceManager instance with the SDK. Once the registration is complete a EventServiceManagerRegistered is posted to the EventBus as returned by IServiceSupport.getEventBus() this event can be used to implement dependency management among various service managers. For an example see the code in com.palomamobile.android.sdk.notification.NotificationManager as it implements its dependency on com.palomamobile.android.sdk.user.IUserManager implementation. After registering this way the service manager is globally available via the IServiceSupport.getServiceManager(Class) method.
        Specified by:
        registerServiceManager in interface IServiceSupport
        Parameters:
        intrface - contract interface implemented by the serviceManager
        serviceManager - instance of the service manager
